# Key Insights

## User Behavior
- A small percentage of users contribute a large portion of total rides, indicating a high-value user segment.
- Most users fall into low to medium engagement categories.

## Engagement Patterns
- Users with higher ride frequency tend to have consistent usage patterns.
- Several users show low or no activity after signup, indicating onboarding drop-offs.

## Ride Characteristics
- Certain vehicle types are used for longer-distance rides, indicating preference for premium or comfort options.
- Some rides exceed the average distance significantly, representing high-value trips.

## Business Recommendations
- Focus retention strategies on high-frequency users.
- Convert medium users into high-engagement users through targeted incentives.
- Re-engage inactive users with offers and notifications.
- Optimize availability of vehicle types for long-distance demand.
